contour.R

leonardo

2020-06-06

Grficos de Contorno para a Log-verossimilhana, dados valores de parmetros, que so \(\sigma^2_1,\sigma^2_2,a,\rho\). Ento para fazer o grfico basta construir uma malha com a funo construct_grid e chamar a funo plot_llike_contour, cujos dois primeiros argumentos devem ter um dos nomes sigma2_1,sigma2_1,a,rho e o terceiro argumento deve ser a malha.

Exemplos :

library(BivMaternEstim)
## Loading required package: fields
## Loading required package: spam
## Loading required package: dotCall64
## Loading required package: grid
## Spam version 2.5-1 (2019-12-12) is loaded.

## Attaching package: 'spam'

##     backsolve, forwardsolve
## Loading required package: maps
## See https://github.com/NCAR/Fields for
##  an extensive vignette, other supplements and source code
library(ggplot2)
source("contour_funs.R")
set.seed(3)
options(ggplot2.continuous.colour="viridis")


n <- 40
coords <- matrix(runif(2*n), ncol = 2)
temp <- rnorm(2*n)
nus_vec <- c(0.5,0.5)


grid_01 <- construct_grid(
  seq(0.01,10,length.out = 15),
  1,
  seq(0.01,10,length.out = 15),
  0.2)

plot_llike_contour("sigma2_1","a",grid_01)

grid_02 <- construct_grid(
  1,
  1,
  seq(0.01,10,length.out = 15),
  seq(0,0.7,length.out = 15)
)

plot_llike_contour("a","rho",grid_02)

grid_03 <- construct_grid(
  seq(0.01,10,length.out = 15),
  seq(0.01,10,length.out = 15),
  1,
  0.2)

plot_llike_contour("sigma2_1","sigma2_2",grid_03)

grid_04 <- construct_grid(
  seq(0.01,10,length.out = 15),
  1,
  1,
  seq(-0.8,0.8,length.out = 15))

plot_llike_contour("sigma2_1","rho",grid_04)

grid_04 <- construct_grid(
  seq(0.01,10,length.out = 15),
  1,
  1,
  seq(-0.8,0.8,length.out = 15))

plot_llike_contour("sigma2_1","rho",grid_04)
